     <p>For those who are interested, we have provided some more information about the study below.</p>

     <h5>Study debrief</h5>

     <p>This study tests memory for word-pairs at delays of 30mins and 24hours.</p> 

     <p>Most memory research and clinical testing looks at memory after 30mins. It is hard to test at extended delays as this normally requires getting participants to return to a memory clinic for repeated testing. As a result less is known about memory development over extended timeframes.</p>

     <p>By using an online test we hope to overcome this problem, allowing a large number of people from the general population to take part.</p>

     <p>By testing at the longer, 24hour delay we hope to identify how memory changes over time.</p> 

     <p>In future we will provide feedback to participants on how their score compares to others. This feature will be added once we have enough data to provide useful comparisons.</p>


